From smoothies, juices, cake toppings or salads, strawberries are known for their high antioxidant properties. Research published at the National library of medicine shows that inflammation occurs when the immune system becomes stressed and overworked. Packed with vitamin C, strawberries promote the proper functioning of the immune system and their anti-oxidant properties, preventing free radicals from damaging cells that trigger new inflammation. Cucumbers, on the other hand, are believed to alleviate symptoms of heart diseases, diabetes, cancer and blood pressure. They are also good for the Skin as they are an excellent source of Vitamin K and Silica, both of which are essential to healthy, glowing skin. Ingredients  Preparation In a bowl, dice up strawberries, cucumber and watermelon. Mix up and enjoy!